<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-759-190  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 759 190.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>IEEE Design andamp; Test of Computers  Oct 1989 v6 n5 p29(11).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>VLSI design and CAD technology in Korea. (very-large-scaleintegration circuits, computer-aided design)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Yu, Young-Uk.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The development of domestic very-large-scale integration (VLSI)integrated circuit (IC) and computer-aided design (CAD)technologies in Korea is being pushed by the country's Ministry ofScience and Technology (MOST) through the National Project onScience and Technology (NPST).andP;  Korea's IC and VLSI designtechnology is about 15 years old, while research and developmentof IC and VLSI CAD is less than ten years old.andP;  The NPST hopes tosee a fully implemented domestic VLSI CAD technology by 1992; aprototype system, EDAS, debuted in 1989.andP;  Other Korean agencies,such as the Electronics and Telecommunications Research Instituteand the Korean Institute of Science and Technology, are supportingthe development of such technologies as bipolar and MOS ICs andsimulation and physical design tools.andP;  A brief history of KoreanVLSI and CAD development efforts is provided.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     KoreaResearch and DevelopmentVery-Large-Scale IntegrationCircuit DesignComputer-Aided DesignProduct DevelopmentHistoryIndustry AnalysisNational GovernmentGovernment Agency.andO;Feature:   illustrationtable.andO;Caption:   Semiconductor process technology in Korea. (table)IC and VLSI design technology in Korea. (table)Key players in the growth of Korean VLSI and CAD technology.andO;(table)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>